  <h2>Browsing</h2>

  <pre><code># List top level
rdc ls /
# в†’ capabilities  info  stats  log  events/  draws/
#   passes/  resources/  textures/  buffers/  shaders/  counters/  current

# Drill into a draw call
rdc ls /draws/5/
# в†’ pipeline/  shader/  bindings/  targets/  postvs  cbuffer/
#   vbuffer  ibuffer  descriptors  pixel/

# Read a shader
rdc cat /draws/5/shader/ps/disasm

# Tree view
rdc tree /draws/5/ --depth 2</code></pre>

  <h2>Binary Safety</h2>
  <p>
    Some VFS nodes contain binary data (textures, buffers). When outputting to
    a TTY, rdc-cli will refuse to print binary content and prompt you to use
    <code>-o</code> to save to a file instead. This protects your terminal.
  </p>

  <pre><code># This will warn about binary content on TTY
rdc cat /textures/5/data

# Use -o to save to file
rdc cat /textures/5/data -o texture.bin</code></pre>

  <h2>Stable Paths</h2>
  <p>
    VFS paths are stable across sessions for the same capture file. This means
    you can use them reliably in scripts and CI pipelines. Event IDs and
    resource IDs come from the capture itself and don't change between runs.
  </p>
